{"key":"post-16223211","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16223211</id>\n<content>For a bulk substrate that size, don't use saran wrap.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cover the tray with foil and crimp it around the edges.&amp;nbsp; You'll get lots of gas exchange because the seal of the foil isn't airtight.&amp;nbsp; Also, I'd poke about half a dozen holes in the foil to boot.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The original poster has drowned the mycelium with a too-wet substrate and cut off its air supply by only having one hole, and it's taped up.&amp;nbsp; If a BRF jar needs four holes for gas exchange, it only makes sense a bulk substrate would need around ten or more times the number of holes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16224269</next>\n<prev>16223073</prev>\n<first>16209695</first>\n<last>16224269</last>\n<when>1336914021</when>\n<utime>05/13/12 04:00 PM</utime>\n</post>"}